# Demo and hero videos

Full detail lives in **demo/WEB_VIDEO_DEMOS.md** (formats, Playwright + ffmpeg, `<video>` embeds, sample assets under **demo/assets/**). When planning or scripting recordings, apply this summary.

## Story and length

- **One idea per video** – single workflow (e.g. upload → edit tags → download), not a full product tour.
- **Front-load the payoff** – strongest frame or end state in the **first few seconds**; then show how you got there if needed.
- **Short for heroes** – about **15–45 seconds** for inline or hero clips; longer only on a dedicated demo page.
- **Rehearse** – avoid dead air and cursor hunting.

## Visual clarity

- UI must stay **legible at embed width** (zoom or window size).
- **Deliberate cursor** – pause on the target before clicking.
- **Clean chrome** – hide unrelated tabs, bookmarks bar, notifications.
- **Consistent framing** across multiple clips.

## Poster, sound, polish

- **Poster** – still that shows the product or the payoff; works as social/thumbnail.
- **Loops** – seamless or end on a calm frame if looping.
- **Audio** – narration when explaining; silent UI demos are fine; no uncleared licensed music.
- **Captions or labels** – support muted viewing and a11y; text large enough for small players.
- **Light polish** – short title or lower-third ok; **no long intros** on short clips; **trim tails** after the success state.

## Delivery (web)

- Ship demos as **MP4 (H.264)** in `<video>` unless the doc specifies otherwise; avoid GIF for real motion demos.
- Prefer **poster + user-initiated play** over aggressive autoplay/preload for energy and UX (see **demo/WEB_VIDEO_DEMOS.md**).
